line_1: They should be good, for then they'd disobey.
line_2: Unless 'twere possible for hell to say,

line_1: When Celadon commands, what god can disobey?
line_2: At his command admit the eye of day:

line_1: Yet I will rather dye than disobey.
line_2: 'Tis a vast Summ, which I can never pay,

line_1: Almighty Jove shall fear to disobey;
line_2: Lo, future times from this instructive day

line_1: And yet the Suns great Maker disobey.
line_2: Ye crawling Worms that bask in the Suns Ray,
He thank'd her care; yet day by day
And devious quit the flowery way,
